<h1>About StackLife</h1>
<p>StackLife is a visualization of Brown Library holdings, both physical and
  digital, in circulating and non-circulating libraries, arranged together by
  <a target="_blank" href="http://www.bpl.org/general/callnumbers.htm">call number</a>
  on a virtual shelf tipped at a 90° angle so that you can read the titles on
  your screen. Since many items in the Library’s collections do not have Library
  of Congress call numbers, this visualization does not include all titles that
  the Library owns. </p>

<p>For example, let's say that you are looking at the book "Splendours of Morocco"
  by Izza Genini and you want to see what other books would be next to it if you
  were standing in front of it at the library.</p>

