</p>

<p>Notice the links <b>More Like This</b> and <b>Browse the Stacks</b> on the
  Tools section of the page.</p>

<ul>
  <li><b>Browse the Stacks</b> will take you to a new page with the books that
  are on the shelf next to "Splendours of Morocco".
  <%= link_to("Try it out!", browse_item_path(id: "b3130393")) %>

  <li><b>More Like This</b> provides similar functionality but in a smaller
  display. Instead of opening a new page, this link will display a small
  stack of books at the bottom of the page.
  <%= link_to("Try it out!", catalog_path(id: "b3130393", nearby: "y")) %>
</ul>

<p>Depending on what kind of search you are doing you might enjoy a full page
  with the stack or the smaller version. They both provide the same information.</p>

<h3>Limitations</h3>
<p>For a variety of reasons, not all the items in the library have call numbers
  and therefore only about 50% of our items are available on the StackLife pages.</p>

<p>Items without call numbers and items in non-LC call number schemes are not
  currently included. However, Annex materials and many digital items are
  browsable alongside the circulating print collection.</p>

